# Styling Rules

## Token Usage
Always import tokens via `@use` — never hardcode raw values.

| Token file | Variables |
|---|---|
| `@/styles/tokens/colors` | `$color-*` |
| `@/styles/tokens/spacing` | `$spacing-*` |
| `@/styles/tokens/typography` | `$font-size-*`, `$font-weight-*`, `$line-height-*`, `$letter-spacing-*` |
| `@/styles/tokens/radius` | `$radius-*` |
| `@/styles/tokens/shadows` | `$shadow-*` |

```scss
// ✅
@use '@/styles/tokens/spacing' as *;
@use '@/styles/tokens/typography' as *;
padding: $spacing-4;
font-size: $font-size-sm;

// ❌
padding: 16px;
font-size: 14px;
```

## Theme-Aware Values
Use CSS custom properties for anything that changes between light and dark themes.

```scss
// ✅ — adapts to theme automatically
color: var(--color-text);
background: var(--color-surface);
border-color: var(--color-border);

// ❌ — hardcoded, breaks dark mode
color: #111827;
```

Available custom properties are defined in `src/styles/theme/light.scss` and `dark.scss`.

## BEM
Follow BEM strictly for all module class names. Always nest elements and modifiers inside the root block class using the `&` prefix — never write them as flat sibling rules.

```scss
// ✅ — nested from the first layer
.card {
  // block base styles

  &--featured { }          // block modifier

  &__header {              // element
    &--sticky { }          // element modifier
  }

  &__body { }
}

// ❌ — flat rules, breaks the nesting convention
.card { }
.card--featured { }
.card__header { }
.card__header--sticky { }
```

Keep nesting to a maximum of 3 levels (block → element → state/modifier). Pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements (`:hover`, `:focus-visible`, `::before`) count as the innermost level.

## Transitions
- Always list individual properties — **never `transition: all`**
- Use short durations for micro-interactions (100–200ms), slightly longer for layout (250–350ms)

```scss
// ✅
transition: background-color 150ms ease, color 150ms ease, box-shadow 150ms ease;

// ❌
transition: all 200ms ease;
```

## Selectors
- Keep nesting shallow (max 3 levels)
- Scope interactive states (`:hover`, `:focus-visible`) inside the base class block
- Gate `:hover` and `:active` with `:not(:disabled)` for accessible interactive elements
